picnic /ˈpɪknɪk/

(picnicking,picnicked,picnics) 

1. N-COUNT When people have a picnic , they eat a meal outdoors, usually in a park or a forest, or at the beach. 野餐 

例： We're going on a picnic tomorrow. 我们明天去野餐。 

2. V-I When people picnic somewhere, they have a picnic. 野餐 

例： Afterwards, we picnicked on the riverbank. 之后，我们在河岸上野餐。

